articles.description: “Sometimes, I pinch myself,” Angela Alvarez, 95, said of her nomination for a Latin Grammy for best new artist.
articles.content:

Growing up in Cuba, Angela Alvarez wanted to be a singer. But after coming to the United States as a young woman, she found herself cleaning a bank in Colorado to make a living… [+6664 chars]
